lt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25464,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/29\/raising-hands-in-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33168,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Description of raising the hands in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 29, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would raise his hands parallel to his shoulders when he entered into prayer, and when he exalted Allah for bowing. When he raised his head from bowing, he would likewise raise his hands and say, \u201cAllah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33168,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33020,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/prophets-dua-after-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33168,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet\u2019s supplication after finishing prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mughirah ibn Shu\u2019bah reported: When the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, finished the prayer and invoked peace, he would say, \u201cThere is no God but Allah, alone without partner. To him belongs the dominion, all praise, and he has power over all things. O Allah, none\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12013,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/04\/repeat-adhan\/","url_meta":{"origin":33168,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Repeat what is said by the caller to prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 4, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen you hear the call to prayer, say something similar to what the caller has said.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 611, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 383 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15394,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/24\/amin-imam-angels\/","url_meta":{"origin":33168,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Ameen: Saying ameen with the Imam and